vivid /ˈvɪvɪd/

1. ADJ If you describe memories and descriptions as vivid , you mean that they are very clear and detailed. (记忆和描写) 清晰的; 生动逼真的 

例： People of my generation who lived through World War II have vivid memories of confusion and incompetence. 我们这一代经历过第二次世界大战的人都还清晰地记得当时的混乱和无能为力。 

2. vividly ADV 清晰地 

例： I can vividly remember the feeling of panic. 我能清晰地回忆起那恐慌感。 

3. ADJ Something that is vivid is very bright in colour. (颜色) 鲜艳的 

例： ...a vivid blue sky. …碧蓝的天空。 

4. vividly ADV 鲜艳地 [ADV -ed/adj] 

例： ...vividly coloured birds. …色彩艳丽的鸟儿。

